{
  "local_port": 56280,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much cubic meter of cement, sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster 1:6 for 950 sq m?",
  "response": "To calculate the volume of cement and sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster with a mix ratio of 1:6 for an area of 950 square meters, we can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Calculate the total volume of plaster required:**\n\n   The thickness of the plaster is 12mm, which is 0.012 meters.\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Volume of plaster} = \\text{Area} \\times \\text{Thickness}\n   \\]\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Volume of plaster} = 950 \\, \\text{m}^2 \\times 0.012 \\, \\text{m} = 11.4 \\, \\text{m}^3\n   \\]\n\n2. **Determine the volumes of cement and sand in the mix:**\n\n   The mix ratio is 1:6, which means for every 1 part of cement, there are 6 parts of sand.\n\n   Total parts of the mix = 1 (cement) + 6 (sand) = 7 parts\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Volume of cement} = \\frac{1}{7} \\times \\text{Total volume of plaster}\n   \\]\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Volume of cement} = \\frac{1}{7} \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}^3 = 1.6286 \\, \\text{m}^3\n   \\]\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Volume of sand} = \\frac{6}{7} \\times \\text{Total volume of plaster}\n   \\]\n\n   \\[\n   \\text{Volume of sand} = \\frac{6}{7} \\times 11.4 \\, \\text{m}^3 = 9.7714 \\, \\text{m}^3\n   \\]\n\nSo, for 12mm cement sand plaster with a 1:6 mix ratio for an area of 950 square meters, you would need approximately:\n\n- **1.63 cubic meters of cement**\n- **9.77 cubic meters of sand**",
